HEADWORD: Coccosteus
<hw>Coc*cos"te*us</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., from
Gr. <?/ grain, seed + <?/ bone.]</ety> <fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>An
extinct genus of Devonian ganoid fishes, having the broad plates about
the head studded with berrylike tubercles.</def>⟦br⟧
